quran[21]{c,v,t}:
  6,74,"Abraham said to his father Azar, “Do you take idols for gods? Indeed I see that you and your people are clearly error.”"
  6,75,"We also showed Abraham the power and the laws of the heavens and the earth, that he might have certainty"
  6,76,"When the night spread over him, He saw a star and said, “This is my Lord.” But when it set he said, “I love not those that set.”"
  6,77,"When he saw the Moon rising in splendor he said, “This is my Lord.” But when the Moon set he said, “Unless my Lord guides me, I will surely be among those who are lost.”"
  6,78,"When he saw the Sun rising in splendor he said, “This is my Lord, this is the greatest of all.” But when the Sun set he said, “O my people, I am indeed free from your giving partners to God"
  6,79,"“For me, I have set my face firmly and truly towards He Who created the heavens and the earth, and never will I give partners to God.”"
  6,80,"His people argued with him and he said, “You argue with me about God, when He has guided me? I do not fear that which you associate with God, unless my Lord wills. My Guardian Evolver comprehends and delivers in His knowledge of all things. Will you then not be advised"
  6,81,"“How could I fear those you associate with God, when you do not fear giving partners to God without permission having been given to you? Which of the two groups has more right to security? Tell me if you know"
  6,82,"“It is those who believe and do not confuse their beliefs with wrong who are truly secure, for they are rightly guided.”"
  6,83,"That was the reasoning about Us which We gave to Abraham for his people. We raise whom We will, degree after degree, for your Lord is full of wisdom and knowledge"
  6,84,"We gave him Isaac and Jacob. All were guided. And before him, We guided Noah, and among his progeny, David, Solomon, Job, Joseph, Moses, and Aaron. We reward those who do right"
  6,85,"And Zachariah and Yahya, and Jesus and Elias, are all in the ranks of the righteous"
  6,86,"And Ishmael and Elisha, Jonas and Lot, and to all We gave favor above the nations"
  6,87,"And from their parents, progeny, and siblings, We chose them, and we guided them to a straight way"
  6,88,"This is the guidance of God. He gives that guidance to whom He pleases among His worshippers. If they were to join other gods with Him, then all that they did would be in vain"
  6,89,"These were those to whom We gave the Book, authority, and the prophetic office. If they reject them, behold, We will entrust their charge to a new people who will not reject them"
  6,90,"These received God's guidance. As for the guidance they received they say, “No reward do I ask of you for this. This is no less than a message to all the worlds.”"
  6,91,"No just estimate of God do they make when they say, “God reveals nothing to a human being.” Say, “Who then sent down the Book that Moses brought, a light and guidance to humanity which you made into scrolls for show, while you conceal much of what is in it, and that which you were taught which you knew not, neither you nor your ancestors?” Say, “God.” Then leave them to plunge in vain discourse and to be trifling"
  6,92,"And this is a book that We have sent down, bringing blessings and reflecting the truth of what came before it, so that you might warn the Mother of Cities, and all around it. Those who believe in the hereafter, believe in this, and are constant in remembering their prayers"
  6,93,"Who can do more wrong than one who invents a lie against God or says, “I have received inspiration,” when he has received none, or who says, “I can reveal the like of what God has revealed.” If you could only see how the wrong-doers fare in the flood of confusion at death. The angels stretch out their hands saying, “Yield up your souls, this day will you receive your reward, a penalty of shame, because you used to tell lies against God, and sarcastically reject His signs.”"
  6,94,"“And behold, you come to us bare and alone, as We created you the first time. You have left behind you, all that We gave to you. We do not see with you your intercessors whom you thought to be partners in your affairs. So now, all relations between you have been cut off, and your desires have left you lost.”"